claim.claim-text:
3. A differential pressure sealing device for use with a piping system containing a flow of fluid passing there through at a first pressure, the sealing device comprising:
a seating mechanism;
a reservoir including a supply of fluid having a fixed volume;
a pressurizing system having a device for compressing the supply of fluid above the first pressure and having an outlet port to supply the pressurized supply of fluid to the seating mechanism at a sealing pressure greater than the first pressure to urge the seating mechanism into a sealing position,
wherein the device for compressing the fluid includes a movable piston and a charging spring, wherein the charging spring exerts a charging force on the piston to pressurize the fluid in the reservoir, wherein the charging spring is held in a compressed position and is further compressed by the pressure of the fluid flowing through the piping system.
